00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:42,560
to take a look at those now.
就来看看这些短语。

164
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,160
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

165
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:50,240
This first phrase is useful in any conversation, I think, especially if you're trying to impress
第一个短语在任何对话中都很实用，我觉得，尤其是你想给某人留下好印象时。

166
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,240
somebody.
某人。

167
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:55,760
So basically, one person in this dialogue says, you know what, you don't know the first
基本上，这段对话中一个人说，你知道吗，你对园艺一窍不通。

168
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,840
thing about gardening.
一窍不通。

169
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,240
That means you don't know anything about gardening.
意思是你对园艺一无所知。

170
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,200
And what does he say in response?
那他怎么回应呢？

171
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:03,000
On the contrary.
恰恰相反。

172
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,000
On the contrary.
恰恰相反。

173
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,880
So the contrary means the opposite.
所以“contrary”意思是相反。

174
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:09,000
So basically this means the opposite is true.
所以基本上就是说事实正好相反。

175
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Right.
对。

176
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,040
You're basically saying, I disagree.
你基本上是在说，我不同意。

177
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,480
What you are saying is false.
你说的是错的。

178
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,640
It's actually the opposite.
实际上正好相反。

179
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:19,320
So maybe I have a feeling, Marco, that it's going to rain tomorrow.
所以，马可，我可能觉得明天会下雨。

180
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:24,240
Actually, on the contrary, I saw in the news that it's going to be very sunny tomorrow.
实际上，恰恰相反，我在新闻里看到明天会是大晴天。

181
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,080
Oh, well, that's good news.
哦，那倒是好消息。

182
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:31,520
So that's a way of maybe politely disagreeing with someone or saying to someone that, well,
所以这是一种礼貌地表示不同意或告诉某人，嗯，

183
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,600
you're wrong.
你错了的方式。

184
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:35,080
It's actually the opposite of what you're saying.
实际上和你说的正好相反。

185
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,080
Okay.
好的。

186
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:40,840
Moving on to our second phrase, it's actually a colloquial way of kind of making fun of
接着看第二个短语，这是一种口语化的方式，用来调侃

187
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:44,320
someone when you say, all right, then, smarty pants.
某人，当你说，好吧，聪明裤。

188
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,560
Okay, smarty pants.
好的，聪明裤。

189
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,920
Don't think about this too much.
别想太多。

190
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:50,000
We're not talking about pants, actually.
我们说的不是裤子。

191
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:55,960
But this is a way of saying, okay, if you're so smart, then tell me that.
但这是种说法，意思是，好吧，如果你这么聪明，那告诉我吧。

192
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,960
It's sarcasm.
这是讽刺。

193
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,960
It's sarcasm.
这是讽刺。

194
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:58,960
Exactly.
没错。

195
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,560
So this person says, oh, actually, I know a lot about gardening.
所以这个人说，哦，实际上我对园艺很了解。

196
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:04,440
And the other person says, oh, really, smarty pants.
另一个人就说，哦，真的吗，聪明裤。

197
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:06,540
So you can actually describe a person in this way.
所以你可以这样形容一个人。

198
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:14,320
Maybe a person that thinks they know a lot or sometimes what you say, a Mr. Know-it-all.
也许是一个自认为懂得很多的人，或者有时你说的“万事通先生”。

199
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:16,040
You also say, it's a smarty pants.
你也可以说，他是个聪明裤。

200
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,040
Right.
对。

201
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:19,880
A person that thinks they know a lot or everything even.
一个自认为懂得很多甚至一切的人。

202
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,880
Right.
对。

203
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,920
Mr. Know-it-all or a smarty pants.
万事通先生或聪明裤。

204
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:23,920
All right.
好的。

205
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:28,160
And our third phrase is interesting because we have a setup here.
第三个短语很有趣，因为我们这里有个设定。

206
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:32,880
When the person says, how will you go about setting up your garden?
当这个人说，你打算怎么着手布置你的花园？

207
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:33,880
Right.
对。

208
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:34,880
Okay.
好的。

209
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,640
So to go about doing something.
所以“to go about doing something”。

210
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:37,920
There's two important parts of this.
这有两个重要部分。

211
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:42,520
So Marco, the first part is how you go about.
所以马可，第一部分是“how you go about”。

212
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,520
This means how you do.
意思是“你怎么做”。

213
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:44,520
Right.
对。

214
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,200
So you can say, how will you do this?
所以你可以说，你会怎么做？

215
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,200
What's your approach?
你的方法是什么？

216
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,200
What's your approach?
你的方法是什么？

217
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:54,120
So how will you go about plus and then the verb in ing.
所以“how will you go about”加上动词的ing形式。

218
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,800
So how will you go about setting up your garden?
所以“how will you go about setting up your garden？”

219
00:09:56,800 --> 00:10:01,880
How will you start or what is your approach to creating your garden?
你怎么开始，或者你创建花园的方法是什么？

220
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:05,720
So maybe Marco, you want to write a book and I can ask you, well, how will you go about
所以也许马可，你想写一本书，我可以问你，嗯，你打算怎么着手

221
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,240
starting your book?
开始写你的书？

222
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,240
Right.
对。

223
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:13,760
Or if I'm writing a book, you can say, how will you go about investigating for your book?
或者如果我在写书，你可以说，你打算怎么着手为你的书做调研？

224
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,560
So what is the approach you're going to take?
所以你要采取什么方法？

225
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,640
How will you do it?
你会怎么做？

226
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:20,600
How do you plan on, how do you plan on doing something?
你打算怎么做某事？

227
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,640
Exactly.
没错。

228
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:27,520
And our final phrase here is a very commonly used for all sorts of situations.
最后一个短语在各种情况下都非常常用。

229
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:32,000
Basically if a person is prepared, you say, well, you have all your bases covered.
基本上，如果一个人准备充分，你会说，嗯，你面面俱到了。

230
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Okay.
好的。

231
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,000
This is a great phrase.
这是个很棒的短语。

232
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,000
It comes right from sports.
它来自体育。

233
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,560
Very common in English to have sports phrases.
英语中体育短语很常见。

234
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:40,000
This comes from the sport baseball.
这个来自棒球运动。

235
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Right.
对。

236
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,880
So in baseball, the field is a diamond.
在棒球中，场地是菱形。

237
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:48,800
There are four corners or four bases and the runners have to go from one base to the other
有四个角或四个垒，跑垒员必须从一个垒到另一个垒，

238
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,440
one, two, three, four, and then they get a point.
一、二、三、四，然后得分。

239
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:55,120
But in this case we're saying the other team, they have their bases covered.
但这里我们说的是对方球队，他们守住了垒。

240
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:57,520
That means they're protecting their bases.
意思是他们在保护自己的垒。

241
00:10:57,520 --> 00:11:02,640
And in speech we say, if you have your bases covered, like you said, Marco, you're very
在口语中我们说，如果你已经面面俱到，就像你说的，Marco，你非常

242
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:03,640
well prepared.
准备充分。

243
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,640
Right.
对。

244
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,880
So you're, you're ready, you're prepared.
所以你已经准备好了，你准备妥当了。

245
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:10,960
You have really planned out and thought of what you're going to do.
你真的计划好了，想好了要做什么。

246
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,000
So you have all your bases covered.
所以你已经面面俱到了。

247
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,960
So Marco, for example, you just told me that it's going to be sunny tomorrow, but I think
所以Marco，比如，你刚才告诉我明天会是晴天，但我认为

248
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,240
it still might rain.
可能还是会下雨。

249
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:21,960
So to have all my bases covered, I'm going to bring an umbrella anyway.
所以为了面面俱到，我还是会带把伞。

250
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:22,960
Just in case.
以防万一。

251
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:23,960
Just in case.
以防万一。

252
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:27,880
Or maybe you have a presentation at work and you've prepared your PowerPoint presentation.
或者也许你在工作上有演示，你准备好了你的PowerPoint演示文稿。

253
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:31,720
You have your, your drawings, your copies, you have everything ready.
你有了图纸、复印件，一切都准备好了。

254
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:34,280
You have all your bases covered for that meeting.
你已经为那次会议面面俱到了。

255
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,280
That's right.
没错。

256
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,280
Okay.
好的。

257
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:39,320
So why don't we go back and listen to our dialogue for the last time and we'll be back
那我们最后再听一遍对话，然后回来再聊一会儿。

258
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:47,160
to talk a little bit more.
再聊一会儿。

259
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:49,600
I've decided to grow my own garden.
我决定自己种个花园。

260
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,600
What?
什么？

261
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,560
You don't know the first thing about gardening.
你对园艺一窍不通。

262
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:55,880
On the contrary, I've been reading a lot of books about the subject.
恰恰相反，我读了很多关于这方面的书。

263
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:56,880
Oh yeah?
哦，是吗？

264
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,760
Tell me then, smarty pants.
那告诉我吧，聪明鬼。

265
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,960
How will you go about setting up your garden?
你打算怎么布置你的花园？

266
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:05,920
Well, first I need to buy some things such as fertilizer, seeds and tools.
嗯，首先我需要买些东西，比如肥料、种子和工具。

267
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,920
What type of tools?
什么类型的工具？

268
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:07,920
You know, the basics.
你知道的，基本工具。

269
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,920
A rake, shovel, spade and a hoe.
耙子、铲子、铁锹和锄头。

270
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:11,920
Right.
对。

271
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:14,080
Well it seems like you have all your bases covered.
嗯，看来你已经面面俱到了。

272
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,080
What's next?
接下来呢？

273
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,360
I'll till the soil and then sow the seeds.
我会翻土，然后播种。

274
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:21,480
I'll then add some fertilizer and voila, gardening all done.
然后加些肥料，瞧，园艺就完成了。

275
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:25,600
Well good luck with your garden, especially considering we're in the dry season and it
嗯，祝你的花园好运，尤其是考虑到我们现在是旱季，接下来三个月

276
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:27,880
won't rain for the next three months.
都不会下雨。

277
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:36,920
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

278
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:40,760
So gardening is actually a very popular thing in many countries.
园艺在很多国家其实很流行。

279
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:46,360
I know many people as well who prefer to have their own personal garden to grow their own
我也认识很多人，他们更喜欢有自己的私人花园来种自己的

280
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:50,320
vegetables which they say taste a lot different from the ones you buy at the supermarket.
蔬菜，他们说这些蔬菜的味道和超市买的大不相同。

281
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,320
They do.
确实如此。

282
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:55,560
I think personally that home grown vegetables, so vegetables that you grow yourself, tend
我个人认为，自家种的蔬菜，也就是你自己种的蔬菜，往往

283
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:58,040
to taste a lot better than the ones you get in the grocery store.
比在杂货店买的要好吃得多。

284
00:12:58,040 --> 00:12:59,040
They also look different.
它们看起来也不一样。

285
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:03,840
They're not as pretty, but that's because they have less chemicals.
它们没那么漂亮，但那是因为它们含的化学物质更少。

286
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:09,120
I think it's a very popular thing and well not only gardening your own vegetables but
我觉得这很流行，而且不仅仅是种自己的蔬菜，

287
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:14,840
some people just enjoy it as a hobby to have some plants and different types of things
有些人只是把它当作一种爱好，在后院种些植物和不同种类的东西。

288
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,840
in their backyard.
在后院种些植物和不同种类的东西。

289
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,080
Yeah, many people say it's very relaxing.
是啊，很多人说这很放松。

290
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:22,880
You get to go outside, you're in the sunshine, it's a very calming activity.
你可以到户外，晒晒太阳，这是一种很平静的活动。

291
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:23,880
It seems like it's very relaxing.
看起来确实很放松。

292
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:26,080
A little bit boring at times.
有时候有点无聊。

293
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:30,560
Basically you're waiting for your plants to grow, but I imagine that once they do, you've
基本上你就是在等植物长大，但我想一旦它们长大了，你

294
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:35,160
accomplished it, it must be great to see that you've actually brought life.
就完成了，看到自己真的创造了生命，一定很棒。

295
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,160
I'm sure.
我肯定。

296
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:38,160
Like 20 minutes every day is not so bad.
比如每天20分钟，也不算太糟。

297
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,160
Yeah.
是啊。

298
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:43,480
It's actually a very interesting hobby and we want to know if in your country, in your
这其实是一个很有趣的爱好，我们想知道在你的国家，你的

299
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,840
town, do you have enough space for a garden?
城镇，你有足够的空间建花园吗？

300
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:49,200
Do you like gardening or maybe growing your own food?
你喜欢园艺或者自己种食物吗？

301
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,520
I think that's a very interesting topic.
我觉得这是个很有趣的话题。

302
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:51,680
Yeah, let us know what you think.
是啊，告诉我们你的想法。

303
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:52,680
Do you do this?
你这样做吗？

304
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:53,960
Yeah, I do.
是的，我这样做。

305
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,720
Our website is EnglishPod.com.
我们的网站是EnglishPod.com。

306
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,720
We hope to see you there.
希望在那里见到你。

307
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,720
All right.
好的。

308
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,720
Bye.
再见。

309
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:22,860
Have a nice time.
祝你愉快。
